paraphare this text the most commonly invoked individual rights in these sort of cases are:

Freedom of expression (protects an individual's right to express themselves freely, including through speech, writing, and artistic expression. The right to privacy may conflict with the right to freedom of expression);

Right to a fair trial (protects an individual's right to a fair and impartial trial. It may conflict with the right to privacy);

Right to information (protects an individual's right to access information held by public authorities. Rightt o privacy may also interfere with the right to information);

Right to property (protects an individual's right to own and use property, including personal and intellectual property. This right may also confluct with the right to privacy).
